[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Location:** The Problem section, paragraph 2
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **The text:** "Surgical video contains a dense record of what happened, when, and how."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Actually, on re-read this is a comma, not an em dash. Let me scan more carefully...
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m After thorough scan: **No em dashes found.** The recipe correctly uses colons, periods, parentheses, and commas throughout. This finding is withdrawn.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Finding 12: Minor Doc-Voice in Prerequisites Table (LOW)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Location:** Prerequisites table, Sample Data row
